metaData.name: description
metaData.value:
Runs a Docker container based on provided image name and the set of options in the attributes: cmd, ports, removeOnClose etc.

The cmd and ports attributes can specify several values by usinga space separator (ie. cmd: ls -lArth, ports: 80 9001:9000)
By default, ports will forward the same port number from host to container. If you wantto differenciate ports, use the hostPort:containerPort syntax.
